{
  "doc_id": "27228",
  "text": "Vicarious trauma refers to the development of negative cognitions in workers who provide treatment to traumatized persons. These negative cognitions are thought to develop as a result of cumulative exposure to clients' traumatic material over time. Vicarious trauma effects develop when workers empathically engage with the traumatized persons that they are working with and are exposed to their explicit accounts of their trauma experience/s [CITATION_1] . Constructivist SelfDevelopment Theory is used to describe how when the worker is exposed to clients' traumatic material overtime, it has a cumulative effect, resulting in cognitive disruptions in the worker's sense of self, view of the world, and relationships [CITATION_2] .",
