      "span_text": "Constructivist SelfDevelopment Theory is used to describe how when the worker is exposed to clients' traumatic material overtime, it has a cumulative effect, resulting in cognitive disruptions in the worker's sense of self, view of the world, and relationships [CITATION_2] ."
